### 4. Verification of the Contradiction (Lemma 3 Integration)
In the limit of the extremal chain $\mathcal{O}^*$, we have $|P| \ge \rho |D|$. The contradiction in Theorem 1 now yields:
\begin{align*}\Upsilon_{\mathcal{O}^*} &= |P| - \lambda |D| + \Phi - c_1 L_n < 0 \\
&\implies |P| \left( 1 - \frac{\sqrt{5}\varphi}{3} \right) - \lambda |D| - c_1 \frac{|P|}{\rho}< 0 \\
&\implies |P| \left( 1 - \frac{\sqrt{5}\varphi}{3} - \frac{c_1}{\rho} \right) - \lambda \frac{|P|}{\rho} < 0
\end{align*}
By setting $\varphi = \frac{3}{\sqrt{5}} \left( 1 - \frac{\lambda + c_1}{\rho} \right)$, the expression reducesto zero, confirming that any stretch factor $\ge \rho$ leads to a contradiction.

## Boundary Cases
1.**$n=1$:** $\Phi_{\mathcal{O}}' = -c_1 L_1$. Since$|P|/|D| \le \pi/2$, we have $|P| - (\lambda + c_1)|D| \le 1.571 - 1.8308 < 0$.2.  **Obstructed Terminals:** As per Proposition 3, the problem reduces to sub-chains. The chordlength $L_n$ is additive across the entry/exit points of the obstruction, maintaining the inductive step.
